ieee8021SpbMib.name: ieee8021SpbMib

revisions.description: 802.1 Shortest Path Bridging MIB Initial Version

ieee8021SpbMib.contactinfo: WG-URL: http://grouper.ieee.org/groups/802/1/index.html WG-EMail: stds-802-1@ieee.org Contact: Don Fedyk Postal: C/O IEEE 802.1 Working Group IEEE Standards Association 445 Hoes Lane P.O. Box 1331 Piscataway NJ 08855-1331 USA E-mail: STDS-802-1-L@LISTSERV.IEEE.ORG

IEEE8021SpbAreaAddress.name: IEEE8021SpbAreaAddress
IEEE8021SpbAreaAddress.description: This identifier is the 3 Byte IS-IS Area Address. Domain Specific part(DSP).

IEEE8021SpbEctAlgorithm.name: IEEE8021SpbEctAlgorithm
IEEE8021SpbEctAlgorithm.description: The 4 byte Equal Cost Multiple Tree Algorithm identifier. This identifies the tree computation algorithm and tie breakers.

IEEE8021SpbMode.name: IEEE8021SpbMode
IEEE8021SpbMode.description: Auto allocation control for this instance of SPB. For SPBV it controls SPVIDs and for SPBM it controls SPSourceID.

IEEE8021SpbEctMode.name: IEEE8021SpbEctMode
IEEE8021SpbEctMode.description: The mode of the Base VID assigned for this instance of SPB. Modes are assigned in the FID to MSTI Allocation table.

IEEE8021SpbDigestConvention.name: IEEE8021SpbDigestConvention
IEEE8021SpbDigestConvention.description: The mode of the current Agreement Digest. This determines the level of loop prevention.

IEEE8021SpbLinkMetric.name: IEEE8021SpbLinkMetric
IEEE8021SpbLinkMetric.description: The 24 bit cost of an SPB link. A lower metric value means better. Value 16777215 equals Infinity.

IEEE8021SpbAdjState.name: IEEE8021SpbAdjState
IEEE8021SpbAdjState.description: The current state of this SPB adjacency or port. The values are up, down, and testing.

IEEE8021SpbmSPsourceId.name: IEEE8021SpbmSPsourceId
IEEE8021SpbmSPsourceId.description: It is the high order 3 bytes for Group Address DA from this bridge. Note that only the 20 bits not including the top 4 bits are the SPSourceID.

IEEE8021SpbDigest.name: IEEE8021SpbDigest
IEEE8021SpbDigest.description: The Topology Agreement digest hex string.

IEEE8021SpbMCID.name: IEEE8021SpbMCID
IEEE8021SpbMCID.description: MST Configuration Identifier digest hex string.

IEEE8021SpbBridgePriority.name: IEEE8021SpbBridgePriority
IEEE8021SpbBridgePriority.description: The Bridge priority is the top 2 bytes of the Bridge Identifier. Lower values represent a better priority.

IEEE8021SpbServiceIdentifierOrAny.name: IEEE8021SpbServiceIdentifierOrAny
IEEE8021SpbServiceIdentifierOrAny.description: The service instance identifier is used at the Customer Backbone port in SPBM to distinguish a service instance. The special value of 0xFFFFFF is used for wildcard. This range also includes the default I-SID.

ieee8021SpbSysAreaAddress.name: ieee8021SpbSysAreaAddress
ieee8021SpbSysAreaAddress.description: The three byte IS-IS Area Address to join. Normally SPB will use area 00:00:00 however if SPB is being used in conjunction with IPV4/V6 it may operate using the IS-IS area address already in use. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbSysId.name: ieee8021SpbSysId
ieee8021SpbSysId.description: SYS ID used for all SPB instances on this bridge. A six byte network wide unique identifier. This is defaulted to the Bridge Address initially but may be overridden. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbSysControlAddr.name: ieee8021SpbSysControlAddr
ieee8021SpbSysControlAddr.description: Group MAC that the ISIS control plane will use. SPB may use a number of different addresses for SPB Hello and LSP exchange. Section 27.2, 8.13.1.5 and Table 8-13 covers the different choices. The choices are as follows: 01:80:C2:00:00:14 = All Level 1 Intermediate Systems 01:80:C2:00:00:15 = All Level 2 Intermediate Systems 09:00:2B:00:00:05 = All Intermediate Systems. 01:80:C2:00:00:2E = All Provider Bridge Intermediate Systems. 01:80:C2:00:00:2F = All Customer Bridge Intermediate Systems. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbSysName.name: ieee8021SpbSysName
ieee8021SpbSysName.description: Name to be used to refer to this SPB bridge. This is advertised in IS-IS and used for management.

ieee8021SpbSysBridgePriority.name: ieee8021SpbSysBridgePriority
ieee8021SpbSysBridgePriority.description: This is a 16 bit quantity which ranks this SPB Bridge relative to others when breaking ties. This priority is the high 16 bits of the Bridge Identifier. Its impact depends on the tie breaking algorithm. Recommend values 0..15 be assigned to core switches to ensure diversity of the ECT Algorithms.

ieee8021SpbmSysSPSourceId.name: ieee8021SpbmSysSPSourceId
ieee8021SpbmSysSPSourceId.description: The Shortest Path Source Identifier. It is the high order 3 bytes for Group Address DA from this bridge. Note that only the 20 bits not including the top 4 bits are the SPSourceID. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbvSysMode.name: ieee8021SpbvSysMode
ieee8021SpbvSysMode.description: Indication of supporting SPBV mode auto(=1)/manual(=2) auto => enable SPBV mode and auto allocate SPVIDs. manual => enable SPBV mode and manually assign SPVIDs. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbmSysMode.name: ieee8021SpbmSysMode
ieee8021SpbmSysMode.description: Indication of supporting SPBM mode auto(=1)/manual(=2) auto => enable SPBM mode and auto allocate SPsourceID. manual => enable SPBM mode and manually assign SPsourceID. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbSysDigestConvention.name: ieee8021SpbSysDigestConvention
ieee8021SpbSysDigestConvention.description: The Agreement Digest convention setting off(=1)/loopFreeBoth(=2)/loopFreeMcastOnly(=3) off => disable agreement digest checking in hellos loopFreeBoth => block unsafe group and individual traffic when digests disagree. loopFreeMcastOnly =>block unsafe group traffic when digests disagree. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTable.name: ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTable
ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTable.description: A Table of multiple logical topologies - MT.

ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTableEntry
ieee8021SpbMtidStaticTableEntry.description: This table configures a MTID to a topology index. A topology index uniquely identifies a specific ISIS topology enabling multiple instances or multiple MTIDs within an instance.

ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryMtid.name: ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryMtid
ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryMtid.description: ISIS Multi Topology Identifier MTID Each MTID defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within one ISIS instance.

ieee8021SpbMTidStaticEntryMtidOverload.name: ieee8021SpbMTidStaticEntryMtidOverload
ieee8021SpbMTidStaticEntryMtidOverload.description: When set for this logical topology this bridge can only originate or terminate traffic. It cannot transit SPB encapsulated traffic. This is the IS-IS overload feature specific to an SPB IS-IS MTID logical topology. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryRowStatus.name: ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryRowStatus
ieee8021SpbMtidStaticEntryRowStatus.description: The object indicates the status of an entry, and is used to create/delete entries. This object is persistent. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbTopIx
ieee8021SpbTopIx.description: Unique identifier of this SPB topology This is index is allocated for this ISIS/MT instance. It is used as an index to most other SPB tables below and to select the exact ISIS instance and which MT instance together.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTable.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTable
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTable.description: This table is for SPB dynamic information. The dynamic information that is sent in this bridges Hellos.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTableEntry
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicTableEntry.description: This table displays the digest information computed for this bridge. A bridge configures this information in MTID 0 only.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryTopIx.description: ISIS-SPB Topology Index identifier Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAgreeDigest.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAgreeDigest
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAgreeDigest.description: The topology agreement digest value. Digest of all topology information, as in clause 28.4.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryMCID.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryMCID
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryMCID.description: The MST Identifier MCID. The MCID is a digest of the VID to MSTID configuration table which determines the Base VIDs enabled for SPBV and SPBM.

ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAuxMCID.name: ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAuxMCID
ieee8021SpbTopIxDynamicEntryAuxMCID.description: The aux MST Identifier for migration. Either MCID or AuxMCID must match for adjacency to form.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticTable.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticTable
ieee8021SpbEctStaticTable.description: The Equal Cost Tree (ECT) static configuration table.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticTableEntry
ieee8021SpbEctStaticTableEntry.description: The Equal Cost Tree static configuration Table defines the ECT-ALGORITHM for the Base VID and if SPBV is used for the SPVID.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryBaseVid.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryBaseVid
ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryBaseVid.description: Base VID to use for this ECT-ALGORITHM. Traffic B-VID (SPBM) or Management VID (SPBV). A Base VID value of 4095 is a wildcard for any Base VID assigned to SPB operation.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryEctAlgorithm.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryEctAlgorithm
ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryEctAlgorithm.description: This identifies the tie-breaking algorithms used in Shortest Path Tree computation. Values range from 00-80-c2-01 to 00-80-c2-16 for 802.1 for each the 16 ECT behaviors. The default is 00-80-c2-01 the LowPATHID. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbvEctStaticEntrySpvid.name: ieee8021SpbvEctStaticEntrySpvid
ieee8021SpbvEctStaticEntrySpvid.description: If SPBV mode this is the VID originating from this bridge. This input is ignored if ieee8021SpbvSysMode is auto(1), but the output always returns the SPVID in use. Otherwise in SPBM this is empty, should be set = 0. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryRowStatus.name: ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryRowStatus
ieee8021SpbEctStaticEntryRowStatus.description: The object indicates the status of an entry, and is used to create/delete entries. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTable.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTable
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTable.description: A table containing Data about the ECT behavior on this bridge

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTableEntry
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicTableEntry.description: This table can be used to check that neighbor bridges are using the same ECT Algorithm.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryBaseVid.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryBaseVid
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryBaseVid.description: The Base VID being queried. Base VID define the mode in the VID to MSTID table.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryMode.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryMode
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryMode.description: The Operating mode of this Base VID. SPBM (=2), SPBV (=3), or disabled or none (1).

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryLocalUse.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryLocalUse
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryLocalUse.description: This value indicates the ECT is in use locally (True/False) for this Base Vid. ECTs may be defined before services are assigned.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryRemoteUse.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryRemoteUse
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryRemoteUse.description: This value indicates the remote ECT is in use (True/False) for this Base Vid. ECTs may be defined before services are assigned.

ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryIngressCheckDi.name: ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryIngressCheckDiscards
ieee8021SpbEctDynamicEntryIngressCheckDi.description: The number of SA check failures on this ECT VID This is referred to as the ingress check and this counter increments whenever a packet is discarded for this VID because it has not come from an interface which is on the shortest path to its SA.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTable.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTable
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTable.description: A table containing the SPB configuration data for a neighbor

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTableEntry
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticTableEntry.description: This table can be used to display the interfaces and metrics of a neighbor bridge.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfIndex.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfIndex
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfIndex.description: The System interface/index which defines this adjacency. A value of 0 is a wildcard for any interface on which SPB Operation is supported.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryMetric.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryMetric
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryMetric.description: The ieee8021Spb metric (incremental cost) to this peer. The contribution of this link to total path cost. Recommended values are inversely proportional to link speed. Range is (1..16777215) where 16777215 (0xFFFFFF) is infinity; infinity signifies that the adjacency is UP, but is not to be used for traffic. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfAdminState.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfAdminState
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryIfAdminState.description: The administrative state of this interface/port. Up is the default. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryRowStatus.name: ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryRowStatus
ieee8021SpbAdjStaticEntryRowStatus.description: The object indicates the status of an entry, and is used to create/delete entries. This object is persistent.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTable.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTable
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTable.description: The SPB neighbor dynamic information table.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTableEntry
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicTableEntry.description: This table is used to determine operational values of digests and interfaces of neighbor bridges.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfIndex.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfIndex
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfIndex.description: System interface/index which defines this adjacency A value of 0 is a wildcard for any interface on which SPB Operation is enabled.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysId.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysId
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysId.description: The SPB System Identifier of this peer. This is used to identify a neighbor uniquely.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPort.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPort
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPort.description: The port number to reach this adjacency.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfOperState.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfOperState
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIfOperState.description: The operational state of this port. up, down or testing (in test).

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysName.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysName
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerSysName.description: IS-IS system name of peer. This is the ASCII name assigned to the bridge to aid management. It is the same as the ieee8021SpbSysName.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAgreeDiges.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAgreeDigest
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAgreeDiges.description: The peer topology agreement digest value (all of the elements defined in clause 28.4). If it does not match this bridge's digest it indicates loss of synchronization.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerMCID.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerMCID
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerMCID.description: The peer MST Identifier MCID. The MCID is a digest of the VID to MSTID configuration table which determines the Base VIDs enabled for SPBV and SPBM.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAuxMCID.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAuxMCID
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerAuxMCID.description: The peer auxiliary MST Identifier. This MCID is used for migration.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryLocalCircuitID.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryLocalCircuitID
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryLocalCircuitID.description: The value used by IS-IS to identify this adjacency locally.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerLocalCircu.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerLocalCircuitID
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerLocalCircu.description: The value used by peer IS-IS to identify this adjacency remotely.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPortIdentifier.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPortIdentifier
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPortIdentifier.description: The value for this bridge which has been selected by IS-IS to form this adjacency if there is more than 1 candidate link.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerPortIdenti.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerPortIdentifier
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryPeerPortIdenti.description: The value for peer port Identifier selected by IS-IS to form this adjacency if there is more than 1 candidate link.

ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIsisCircIndex.name: ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIsisCircIndex
ieee8021SpbAdjDynamicEntryIsisCircIndex.description: The isisCircTable reference. This allows cross referencing to an IS-IS MIB.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeTable.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeTable
ieee8021SpbTopNodeTable.description: Table of network specific bridge information.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeTableEntry
ieee8021SpbTopNodeTableEntry.description: This table is used to display system level information about bridges in the network.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysId.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysId
ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysId.description: The IS-IS System ID of a bridge in the SPB LSP database and hence the network. A value of 0 is a wildcard for all System identifiers.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryBridgePriority.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryBridgePriority
ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntryBridgePriority.description: The Bridge Priority of the bridge in the LSP database. This is a 16 bit quantity which ranks this SPB Bridge relative to others when breaking ties. This priority is the high 16 bits of the Bridge Identifier. Its impact depends on the tie breaking algorithm. Recommend values 0..15 be assigned to core switches to ensure diversity of the ECT Algorithms.

ieee8021SpbmTopNodeEntrySPsourceID.name: ieee8021SpbmTopNodeEntrySPsourceID
ieee8021SpbmTopNodeEntrySPsourceID.description: The Shortest Path Source Identifier. It is the high order 3 bytes for Group Address DA from this bridge. Note that only the 20 bits not including the top 4 bits are the SPSourceID.

ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysName.name: ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysName
ieee8021SpbTopNodeEntrySysName.description: The System Name. A Human readable name of this bridge This is used to aid in management and is used in place of the System identifier in many commands and displays.

ieee8021SpbTopEctTable.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctTable
ieee8021SpbTopEctTable.description: Table of all ECT use in the network

ieee8021SpbTopEctTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctTableEntry
ieee8021SpbTopEctTableEntry.description: This table lists bridges and the ECT Algorithms configured and in use.

ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbTopEctEntrySysId.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctEntrySysId
ieee8021SpbTopEctEntrySysId.description: The system ID which is using a particular ECT. A value of 0 is a wildcard for all System identifiers.

ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryBaseVid.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryBaseVid
ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryBaseVid.description: Base VID related to this algorithm In the case of SPBM this is the B-VID that carries traffic for this ECT-ALGORITHM. In the case of SPBV this is the Base-VID used for management. A Base VID value of 4095 is a wildcard for any Base VID assigned to SPB operation.

ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryEctAlgorithm.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryEctAlgorithm
ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryEctAlgorithm.description: The ECT-ALGORITHM in use. A 32 bit number. The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.; the upper 24 bits are an OUI and the lower 8 bits are an index. This creates a world-wide unique identity for the computation that will be using the VID thus ensuring consistency.

ieee8021SpbvTopEctSysMode.name: ieee8021SpbvTopEctSysMode
ieee8021SpbvTopEctSysMode.description: Indication of supporting SPBV mode auto(=1)/manual(=2) auto => SPBV mode and auto allocate SPVIDs. manual => SPBV mode and manually assign SPVIDs.

ieee8021SpbvTopEctEntrySpvid.name: ieee8021SpbvTopEctEntrySpvid
ieee8021SpbvTopEctEntrySpvid.description: SPVID in V mode The VID this bridge will use to originate traffic using this ECT-ALGORITHM when running in SPBV mode.

ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryLocalUse.name: ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryLocalUse
ieee8021SpbTopEctEntryLocalUse.description: Is this ECT-ALGORITHM in use locally by advertising bridge :- TRUE or FALSE. This is used to help with disruption-free migration between ECT-ALGORITHMs. Changes are only allowed if this flag is FALSE.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTable.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTable
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTable.description: A Table of edges in network (not duplicated), but each link will appear as two entries, one ordered {near-far}, the other {far-near}.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTableEntry
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeTableEntry.description: The table lists information about bridge edges (links).

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryTopIx.description: The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdNear.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdNear
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdNear.description: The System ID of near bridge (the bridge reporting the adjacency). A value of 0 is a wildcard for all System identifiers.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdFar.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdFar
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntrySysIdFar.description: The System ID of far bridge (the neighbor of the bridge reporting). A value of 0 is a wildcard for all System identifiers.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricNear2Far.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricNear2Far
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricNear2Far.description: The metric used on this edge advertised by near end This is the raw value. If it is less than the MetricFar2Near (below), the MetricFar2Near is used as the SPF metric in both directions.

ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricFar2Near.name: ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricFar2Near
ieee8021SpbTopEdgeEntryMetricFar2Near.description: The metric used on this edge advertised by far end This is the raw value. If it is less than the MetricNear2Far (above), the MetricNear2Far is used as the SPF metric in both directions.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTable.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTable
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTable.description: All SPBM PBB encapsulated services in this network.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTableEntry
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvTableEntry.description: This table displays information about PBB services received in the LSP data base. The Service Identifier is associated with the MAC address and Base VID of the bridge that originates or terminates the service.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryTopIx.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryTopIx
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryTopIx.description: Entry of one The ISIS Topology Index identifier to which this instance belongs. Each Topology Index defines logical topology and is used to enable multiple SPB instances within several ISIS instances.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntrySysId.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntrySysId
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntrySysId.description: The System identifier this service originates/terminates on. A value of 0 is a wildcard for all System identifiers.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsid.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsid
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsid.description: An ISID (service) originating/terminating on this bridge. A value of 0 is a wildcard for any ISID.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryBaseVid.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryBaseVid
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryBaseVid.description: The Base VID associated with this service. The Base VID determines the ECT Algorithm that is associated with this service. A Base VID value of 4095 is a wildcard for any Base VID assigned to SPB operation.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryMac.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryMac
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryMac.description: The MAC address associated with a service. An additional nodal MAC address by which an I-SID can be reached may be advertised, in which case traffic to this MAC follows a forwarding path identical to that taken to reach the corresponding SYSID (nodal) MAC. If no additional MAC is advertised this will be the SYSID MAC. A value of 0 is a wildcard for the MAC address.

ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsidFlags.name: ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsidFlags
ieee8021SpbmTopSrvEntryIsidFlags.description: A pair of flags defining the attributes of this service. These specify independently whether ingress frames to the SPBM region should be transmitted within it, and whether frames received from the SPBM region are required egress it.

ieee8021SpbvTopSrvTable.name: ieee8021SpbvTopSrvTable
ieee8021SpbvTopSrvTable.description: The SPBV group services in this network

ieee8021SpbvTopSrvTableEntry.name: ieee8021SpbvTopSrvTableEntry
